videos.description: London Perrantes 3-pointer forces Louisville to call an early timeout.
videos.headline: Perrantes has Virginia  off to fast start against Louisville

videos.description: D. Mitchell uses his moves to finish off this layup
videos.headline: Donovan Mitchell shows his skill on nice layup

videos.description: Jaylen Johnson finishes off the alley-oop on a perfect pass by David Levitch.
videos.headline: Johnson throws down nice alley-oop dunk for Louisville

videos.description: M. Diakite made Dunk. Assisted by D. Hall.
videos.headline: Mamadi Diakite throws down strong dunk for Virginia

videos.description: Jaylen Johnson finishes off another alley-oop on a lob from David Levitch.
videos.headline: Johnson throws down another huge alley-oop for Louisville

videos.description: Louisville head coach Rick Pitino talks about his teams ability to use great spacing and explains the need to limit fouls moving forward
videos.headline: Louisville head coach Rick Pitino talks about his teams great spacing in the first half and explains the need to limit fouls moving forward

videos.description: Virginia forces Louisville into an early second half timeout after made baskets by London Perrantes and Marial Shayok
videos.headline: Virginia strikes quickly to open second half

videos.description: Mamadi Diakite takes the jumper that has the crowd groaning until it goes in to cap a 13-2 Virginia run.
videos.headline: Mamadi Diakite jumper caps 13-2 run for Virginia

videos.description: Failed press coverage leads to a pair of Virginia dunks that leave Louisville head coach Rick Pitino speechless.
videos.headline: Virginia dunks on defensive breakdowns leave Pitino speachless
Postgame Breakdown with Virginia guard London Perrantes on the teams 2nd half adjustments that led to their 71-55 win over Louisville
